<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/38203AJPPLKJKTHNBTMCCGLVLBJSTKLSB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "2026 Max and Pearl Herman Lecture";
  schema:description """
	You're invited to join us at the next lecture in the Max and Pearl Herman Lecture Series in Judaic Studies. The 2026 Lecture features <span class=\"BoldText\">Dr. Norman Ravvin</span>, author of <span class=\"ItalicText\">Who Gets In: An Immigration Story (University of Regina Press)</span>.  Dr. Norman Ravvin will discuss this deeply personal family memoir, which tells the story of his grandfather’s struggle against xenophobic and anti-Semitic government policies, and investigates the true character of nation-building in Canada, directly challenging its reputation as a benevolent, tolerant, and multicultural country.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>About the Author<span><br/></span>Dr. Norman Ravvin is the award-winning author of <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Girl Who Stole Everything; Hidden Canada: An Intimate Travelogue; A House of Words: Jewish Writing, Identity, and Memory; and Who Gets In: An Immigration Story.</span><span><br/></span>Born in Calgary, he now lives in Montreal, Quebec.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Free admission by pre-registration only.  To register, please visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.uregina.ca/alumni-and-friends/events/registration/2026/may/herman-lecture.html\">the University of Regina&#39;s registration website.</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://uofrpress.ca/Books/W/Who-Gets-In\">Learn more about Who Gets In: An Immigration Story.</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This event is presented by the University of Regina's <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://casls-regina.primo.exlibrisgroup.com/discovery/collectionDiscovery?vid=01CASLS_REGINA:01CASLS_REGINA&amp;collectionId=81320629280003476\">Max &amp; Pearl Herman Endowment Fund.</a>
""";
