<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/22002ATKNPKBTHDMHVQBTRKTKGPVTGDQN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Beatlemania Revisited";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">VaughnCo Entertainment is proud to present<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>BEATLEMANIA REVISITED!<span><br/></span>“It’s been a hard day’s night, and I’ve been working like a dog…”</span><span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Music fans will easily recall these famous lyrics sung by the legendary <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">John Lennon</span></span> in the timeless Beatles’ hit <span class=\"ItalicText\">‘A Hard Day’s Night’</span>, a worldwide chart-topping single for the Liverpool group back in 1964. The Beatles are the most commercially successful and critically acclaimed act in the history of popular music and according to Guinness World Records, their recordings have sold over one billion units. Originally formed in 1960, the group developed their musical skills and reputation through extensive live performances that culminated into riotous enthusiasm by screaming fans wherever they went, a phenomenon that became known as <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">‘Beatlemania!’</span></span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">‘Beatlemania Revisited’</span></span>, an international touring show, recreates the look, sound and excitement of the fab four’s live performances. This unique musical and theatrical event features a combination of talented European and North American cast members in the roles of <span class=\"ItalicText\">John, Paul, George and Ringo</span>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Beatlemania Revisited</span></span> is a family oriented, audience-interactive performance that will have fans laughing, singing, dancing and clapping along throughout the show. Musically, the show features ‘note-for-note’ song recreations by the amazing cast who are further augmented with full costumes along with vintage instruments and equipment. Focusing mainly on <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">The Beatles’</span></span> live performances, the show kicks off with their electrifying first appearance on the Ed Sullivan television show in February 1964, taking the audience through five years of the Beatles’ era concluding with their famous January 1969 ‘roof top’ concert. Along the way, <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Beatlemania Revisited</span></span> takes in a total of 35 songs, including <span class=\"ItalicText\">‘I Want To Hold Your Hand’, ‘Ticket to Ride’, ‘Yesterday’.  ‘Penny Lane, ‘Hey Jude’, ‘Something’, ‘Let It Be’</span> and many other timeless favourites.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Young or old, don’t miss the opportunity to experience this fab new show!!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are $59.94 inclusive of fees and taxes. Seating is assigned.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All sales are final; no refunds issued.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
