<http://www.spektrix.com/darkehallsociety/event/24001ABMNLGCGVMRMGTMJKPBQCNHQQLMH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Caity Gyorgy with the Regina Jazz Orchestra";
  schema:description """
	Experience an unforgettable evening with the <span class=\"BoldText\">Regina Jazz Orchestra</span> joined by the sensational <span class=\"BoldText\">Caity Gyorgy</span>, a three-time JUNO Award-winning vocalist. Gyorgy’s unparalleled vocal prowess will blend seamlessly with the orchestra’s rich, dynamic arrangements, creating a night of exquisite jazz. Don’t miss this chance to witness a masterful fusion of sophisticated sounds and stellar talent.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Caity Gyorgy (pronounced George) is a 3-time JUNO award-winning Canadian vocalist known for singing bebop and swing music. She has performed at jazz clubs and festivals across Canada, Mexico, Finland, Japan, and the USA and has worked and recorded with incredible musicians, including Christine Jensen, Pat LaBarbera, Jocelyn Gould, Ira Coleman, The UMO Helsinki Jazz Orchestra, Bryn Roberts, and Joe LaBarbera, to name a few.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In addition to performing, Caity is an award-winning songwriter and composes music and lyrics in the style of the Great American Songbook. She is also a sought-after clinician and is on faculty as a vocal jazz instructor at the Yukon Summer Music Camp in Whitehorse, Yukon, and the Interprovincial Music Camp in McKellar, Ontario. She is currently signed to Brooklyn label La Reserve Records and has released several albums of original and standard music with them including her three JUNO award-winning albums “Now Pronouncing”(2021), “Featuring” (2022) and “Hello! How Are You?” (2024) and her JUNO-nominated album with pianist Mark Limacher titled “You’re Alike, You Two”. (2023). <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Her new album, “Asking For Trouble” features the music of Frank Loesser played in a duo setting with Mark Limacher and was released on April 11, 2025. Her next album, “Caity Gyorgy with Strings: Arranged and Conducted by Mark Limacher”, will be released on August 22, 2025.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Tickets are $48.84 for adults and $21.09 for students, inclusive of fees and taxes.  Seating is not assigned.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-30T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
